{{Infobox video game | developer = Pocket Gems | released = February 2014 | genre = Interactive fiction | modes = Mobile }}{{notability|1=Products|date=September 2017}}
'''Episode''' is an interactive story app developed by American game developer Pocket Gems.<ref>{{cite news|title=‘Pretty Little Liars’ Offshoot Debuts on Episode’s Interactive Story App|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/pretty-little-liars-episode-app-1201941957/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pocket Gems’ Episode brings back Clueless as an interactive mobile game|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/08/16/pocket-gems-episode-brings-back-clueless-as-an-interactive-mobile-game/|work=[[VentureBeat]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pocket Gems Reviving 'Mean Girls' With New Mobile Game|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/pocket-gems-reviving-mean-girls-801605|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=How Episode became the world's biggest interactive fiction platform|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/293928/How_Episode_became_the_worlds_biggest_interactive_fiction_platform.php|work=[[Gamasutra]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pocket Gems Launches Episode, A Platform For Interactive Mobile Stories|url=https://techcrunch.com/2014/02/20/pocket-gems-launches-episode/|work=[[TechCrunch]]|accessdate=21 September 2017}}</ref>
The app is a storytelling network and platform that features interactive stories built from the ground up for mobile. Users enter one of 84,000 stories and make choices as the storyline progresses. With over 125 million installs, there have been over 4.4 billion episodes viewed on Episode so far, adding up to over 76,000 years of combined viewing time. The product also has a UGC creation platform that enables users to create their own stories, 12 million of which have registered.
Episode features four three types of stories:
* User generated * In-house originals * IP licensed (studio and celebrity)
Some notable IP stories include Demi Lovato: Path to Fame, Pretty Little Liars, Clueless, Pitch Perfect In Deep Treble, Cameron Dallas: It Started With a Lie, and Falling For the Dolan Twins.
