[[File:Tim Hetherington Trust logo.jpg|thumb]] {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Use British English|date=October 2015}} The '''Tim Hetherington Trust''' was set up in 2012<ref>{{cite web|url = http://apps.charitycommission.gov.uk/Accounts/Ends48/0001152248_AC_20130630_E_C.PDF | access-date = 7 October 2015 | author = Tim Hetherington Trust | publisher = [[Charity Commission for England and Wales]] | title = The Tim Hetherington Charitable Trust Unaudited Trustees' Report and Financial Statements for the Period Ended 30 June 2013}}</ref> by the late [[Tim Hetherington]]'s parents Judith and Alistair.<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/greater-manchester-news/how-tims-eye-picture-still-3817669 | date = 15 May 2013 | access-date = 7 October 2015 | first = Tom | last = Brooks-Pollock | newspaper = [[Manchester Evening News]] | title = How Tim’s eye for a picture is still helping blind African children}}</ref> [[Stephen Mayes]] has been its executive director since 2013.<ref name="liverpool-echo">"[http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/whats-on/tim-hetherington-photo-exhibition-set-5826953 Images of war captured in Tim Hetherington photo exhibition]", [[Liverpool Echo]]. Accessed 29 June 2014.</ref><ref name="padley-bjp-trust">{{cite web|url = http://www.bjp-online.com/2015/02/tim-hetherington-trust-shortlist-new-award/ | date = 3 February 2015 | access-date = 8 October 2015 | first = Gemma | last = Padley | magazine = [[British Journal of Photography]] | title = Tim Hetherington Trust unveils new award shortlist}}</ref> The Trust's website states its mission is "to preserve the legacy of Tim’s professional life as a visual storyteller and human rights advocate" including "the support and nurture of new work that continues the ideals demonstrated by Tim with special emphasis on humanitarian and social concerns".<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.timhetheringtontrust.org/about-us/ | access-date = 8 October 2015 | publisher = Tim Hetherington Trust | title = Tim Hetherington}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://mediastorm.com/blog/2015/02/03/fight-hate-with-love-shortlisted-for-tim-hetherington-visionary-award/ | date = 3 February 2015 | access-date = 8 October 2015 | publisher = MediaStorm | title = “Fight Hate With Love” Shortlisted for Tim Hetherington Trust Visionary Award}}</ref>
==Tim Hetherington Visionary Award== In 2014 the Trust founded the Visionary Award for innovation in visual storytelling. It awards £20,000 and a mentor to one artist or duo to work on their proposed project. It seeks to encourage artists and journalists whose work crosses the boundaries of art, reportage and technology to innovate in terms of Hetherington's goal of "how do we use media in a way that is really effective?".<ref name="padley-bjp-trust" /><ref name="bjp-162">{{cite journal | year = 2015 | title = Tim Hetherington Visionary Award | periodical = [[British Journal of Photography]] | volume = 162 | issue = 7834 | pages = 12, 13 | publisher = Incisive Financial Publishing Limited}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = http://time.com/3692898/tim-hetherington-trust-unveils-visionary-award-shortlist/ | date = 3 February 2015 | access-date = 8 October 2015 | first = Olivier | last = Laurent | magazine = [[Time (magazine)|Time]] | title = Tim Hetherington Trust Unveils Visionary Award Shortlist}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.vanityfair.com/culture/photos/2015/02/tim-hetherington-trust-finalists | first = David | last = Friend | access-date = 8 October 2015 | publisher = [[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]] | title = Showcasing the Finalists for the Award to Honor Tim Hetherington}}</ref>
===Recipients=== *2015: [[Eline Jongsma]] and [[Kel O'Neill]] for ''The Ark''<ref name="padley-bjp-award">{{cite web|url = http://www.bjp-online.com/2015/04/tim-hetherington-visionary-award-announces-winner-of-20000-grant/ | date = 2 April 2015 | access-date = 8 October 2015 | first = Gemma | last = Padley | magazine = [[British Journal of Photography]] | title = Tim Hetherington Visionary Award gives £20,000 grant to experimental conservation documentary}}</ref> *2016: Dominic Bracco II for ''The Backs Of Men''<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.bjp-online.com/2016/05/dominic-bracco-the-tim-hetherington-trust-visionary-award-winner-i-saw-people-i-love-do-horrific-things/ | date = 4 May 2016 | accessdate = 25 April 2017 | author = Izabela Radwanska Zhang | magazine = [[British Journal of Photography]] | title = Dominic Bracco, the Tim Hetherington Trust Visionary Award winner: “I saw people I love do horrific things”}}</ref> *2017: Omar Imam for ''Syrialism (or What Syrians Want)''<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.timhetheringtontrust.org/news-and-calendar/2017/04/visionary-award-2017-presented-omar-imam | date = 20 April 2017 | accessdate = 25 April 2017 | publisher = Tim Hetherington Trust | title = Visionary Award 2017 presented to Omar Imam}}</ref> *2018: [[Laia Abril]] for ''A History Of Misogyny, Chapter 2: On Rape Culture''<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2018-05-26|title=Visionary Award 2018: Laia Abril 17th May 2018, London|url=http://www.timhetheringtontrust.org/news-and-calendar/2018/05/visionary-award-2018-laia-abril|website=[[Tim Hetherington Trust]]}}</ref>
